The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 January is 175,835 (20,266 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 January, there were 7,093 new confirmed cases (817.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 January, there were 11,105 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 36% (4,012 fewer cases).
